        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1621690513" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17649819061170939868">This book should be required reading for all US citizens. In the United States we confuse country with government. We as citizens owe no loyalty to our government only to what is right. If our government commits atrocities in our name it is a citizen&apos;s duty to demand better. This goes to the heart of Howard Zinn&apos;s essays. They ask what does it mean to be an engage citizen? What relationship does government have to the individual? How much are we being lied to? What can we do about it? </span>
